LLMs are central to Generative AI, and this is a very common interview question area
What is an LLM?

LLM (Large Language Model) is a type of AI model that:
-> Understands and generates human-like text
Examples:
ChatGPT
- GPT models (GPT-3, GPT-4, etc.)
- Google Gemini


What they can do:
- Write emails
- Generate code
- Summarize documents
- Translate languages

LLMs are trained to:
-> Predict the next word in a sentence
Example :
Input: "DevOps is important because"
Output: "it improves automation and reliability"

| Feature  | Traditional Model | LLM                                 |
| -------- | ----------------- | ----------------------------------- |
| Output   | Label / number    | Full text                           |
| Data     | Structured        | Unstructured (text)                 |
| Size     | Small             | Very large (billions of parameters) |
| Use case | Prediction        | Conversation, generation            |

